quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  61,1,"All that is in the heavens and all that is on earth extols Allah's glory. He is the Most Mighty, the Most Wise.",footnotes:182040:1
  61,2,"Believers, why do you profess that which you do not practise?"
  61,3,"It is most loathsome in the sight of Allah that you should profess what you do not practise.",footnotes:182041:1
  61,4,"Allah indeed loves those who fight in His Way as though they are a solid wall cemented with molten lead.",footnotes:182042:1
  61,5,"And call to mind when Moses said to his people: “O my people, why do you torment me when you know well that I am Allah's Messenger to you?” So when they deviated, Allah made their hearts deviant. Allah does not direct the evil-doers to the Right Way.",footnotes:182043:1,footnotes:182044:2